				<p>This is a cool cloaking device, but it doesn't actually make anything invisible any more than my TV makes the wall behind it invisible. Fortunately, Infra-red is often monocular so it can still be a fairly effective technology. </p>
<p></p>
<p>As for defeating US "Smart Weapons", that's unlikely. Laser guided weapons will still be fine, and any radio guided weapons will probably not see much reduced effect either. Also, the US isn't exactly engaging in warfare with countries bringing the latest and greatest to the field, so it's not like we would throw our hands up and start over - and given how much of our weapons stockpile the US is actively destroying, I think it's just as well not to have a reason to switch technology again. </p>
